<br>
Let me say firstly that I like the idea/concept of this expansion, tho a few &quot;possible problems&quot; need to get cleared up for us consumers(why is SOE always so vague about new expansions?) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think the biggest concern I and most of you have is &quot;instancing&quot; of the dungeons. 40 dungeons x max of 6 people per party = 240 people max using all the dungeons at once. If the programmers have any brains left in their heads they will allow more then 1 instance(&quot;version&quot;) of each dungeon, otherwise you have a max of 240 people that can be accomodated by all the dungeons at any given time. Who wants to take odds that there will be more then 240 people wanting to try the new dungeons on release day of the expansion? If they only allow 1 instance/version of each dungeon per 45-90 min period, you may have alot of pissed off people on release day. If they are smart about this, and Im hoping they are, they will allow like up to 3 instances of each dungeon, boosting the max number of people that can play simultaneously to 720.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>All members of the group will be able to enter that dungeon to face the dangers there, but other player characters will not....Parties of five or six characters will be able to travel the Lost Dungeons.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This opens so many questions and concerns about how many people exactly can go in. What happens if, after you accept the quest but before you actually go INTO the dungeon, people in your group have to leave for some reason? Are we forced to go all the way BACK to the quest giver and look for new people again? Sounds like a possible big timesink in travel time if the answer to this is yes. They need to find a way to allow new people to join the group AFTER you accept the quest but BEFORE you actually go into the dungeon. I dont want to travel 6+ zones with my group of 5-6 and finally get to the outside of the dungeon, only to have people leave for some reason, then we have to trudge all the way back to the quest-giver and find more people to start a NEW group. Again, if they only allow 1 instance of each dungeon, your shit outta luck if you cant actually do the dungeon after all. You have to get back into the waiting list at the end and hope people dont leave again when its your turn to do the dungeon.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;As you prove yourself to them, they'll allow you to pick from a large variety of rewards.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sounds like going into McDonalds and ordering a meal off the menu lol. Im wondering how they'll implement the &quot;pick from a large variety of rewards&quot; thing. will it be a &quot;window-list&quot; of items each person can pick from? Also, can each item on the &quot;reward list&quot; be chosen more then once? Otherwise you may have greedy people picking the best items leaving the lesser stuff to the rest of the party.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Tell us about the new in-game interface that tracks players' progression through the dungeons? Shawn Lord: It's really too early to discuss this. We will be working more in the future to track players' accomplishments, but what this will mean to them is still a bit of a secret.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This could be a 2 edged sword. What it sounds like is a &quot;save game&quot; feature after you finish each dungeon in the overall &quot;quest&quot;. But what happens if people have to leave midway thru the dungeon leaving you with less then 5-6 people? Does it save each person at a specific dungeon-location-level? What happens if each person progresses and gets saved at different &quot;levels&quot; of the quest? Do the people that are farther ahead in the &quot;quest&quot; have to go back in &quot;content/quest level&quot; if they wanna group with a friend that isnt as far ahead as them in the overall quest? Really wondering how theyre gonna do this &quot;progression tracking&quot; system.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How do players physically jump into the new locations? Do they need special items to gain access?  Shawn Lord: The NPC that gives you the adventure will also give you an idea about where that adventure will be located. Getting there is up to you. In fact, some of the challenge to a given adventure may be getting to it. Once your group arrives at the proper location, you will find an entrance. No special items are needed; you just need to have been sent on their adventure by the proper NPC.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, what happens if, after accepting the &quot;quest&quot; more then a few people have to suddenly leave? Are you sol for that dungeon crawl? If you are then that means lost time in travelling to said dungeon, and you have to find new people to make the 5-6 person group and go BACK to the quest giver and start over. If you HAVE to have 5-6 people in the group and cant add new people after you accept the quest, then this would truly suck. However, if they allow you to add new people somehow before you enter the dungeon, or allow you to have less then 5-6 people in the group, then I guess that would solve it.<br>
Whether you can have less then 5-6 people in the group, or if you can add new members after accepting the quest but before you actually enter the dungeon is a BIG question for me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Will you have to &quot;wait in line&quot; while other groups are in the dungeons?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, I hope not, seeing as this will be a new expansion, everyone and their mom will be there to try it out on the first few days. Hopefully they will have more then 1 &quot;instance&quot; of the same types of dungeons.<br>
<br>
Another question I have is will loot you get in the dungeons be &quot;tradeable&quot;(hi Bazaar mule loot) or no drop? I vote no drop but I've never been a big fan of the bazaar hehe.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;I wished they would of addressed CR's in the article, with the information I have presently, (admittedly not much) CR's look to be a huge pain.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, from the sounds of it, the only pain in doing CR's will be the travel time back to the dungeon, if you dont have a rezzer in the group. You wont have to worry about getting back to your body in the dungeon once you're back inside the dungeon, as all previous mobs will already be dead if you killed them all. You just walk back down to your body. If it works this way though, I would kind of hate it actually. Some of my favorite memories were having to do a CR deep in a dungeon w/o a rezzer and no way to get back down to your body easily(hi Sebilis! lol).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;I would hate to show up only to find my team is #39 on the waiting list.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, I think this is one of my biggest questions about the expansion. Waiting lines are no thx. Especially on release day of the expansion when everyone and their mom wants to try out the new dungeons at the same time. Will they allow more then 1 instance of the same &quot;dungeon&quot;?? Big if, and I hope the answer is yes. If not, then you'll have 40 dungeons x 6 people per group = 240 people can only use the new expansion at a time max. Not very big numbers imo.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and these are just dungeons - i'm pretty sure big bosses will still require 2-3groups<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Do you mean the big bosses at the end of each dungeon? If so, I dont see where they said you can have 2-3 groups for it in the article. If you're talking about something else, sorry for the mis-quote hehe.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the long post, I like the idea of the new expansion, but theres so many questions that need to be answered before the release date. Tho knowing this games' track record, we wont get much more explanation than what we have, and there will be alot of turmoil and needed patches everyday for the first 2 weeks after release.<br>
<br>
Hopefully they allow more then 1 instance of each dungeon(like maybie 3 or so). Hopefully they figured on every player on the server wanting to try the dungeons at the same time, and made preparations to allow that. Hopefully. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
